cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SDQ 

The paper is about speaker verification using deep feature learning, which falls under the sub-category of speech processing and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper investigates the robustness of the system, which could fall under the sub-category of quality control and testing, making cs.SDQ (Sound and Quality Control) a possible sub-category.
